<opener><dateline><date>13<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> June</date></dateline>
<salute>My Pr</salute></opener>
<p>We are likely to be more &amp; more scurried
<lb/> &amp; later letters will very likely be impossible
<lb/>for 3 or 4 days <add>at a time</add>  so you must not be anxious about
<lb/>things  </p>
<p>If you have time you might send out
<lb/>some chocolate, the harder &amp; more solid the 
<lb/>better.  </p>
<p>Someone the other day showed me a 
<lb/>steel waistcoat which is shrapnel proof. If
<lb/>you should hear of such a thing you might send
<lb/>it out soon. I could not see it advertised, but
<lb/>the Government is beginning to turn them out
<lb/>I believe &amp; they might be useful in certain
<lb/>eventualities tho' probably one would very seldom
        
    

    
         
        <pb n="6280" facs="#L1916_2267_img_6280"/>
        
        
           
            this must have helped the entente. </p>
        
    
